sect1.para:
As of April 2020, the census recorded a resident population of 331,449,281 in the 50 states and the national capital of Washington, D. C., reflecting an increase of 7.4%, or 22,703,743, over that of 2010 (U. S. Department of Commerce: U. S. Census Bureau 
               2022
            ). Also, as of 2022, nearly 46.2 million immigrants lived in the United States, the most in U. S. history.

listitem.para:
6. Some other race was included for people who are unable to identify with the other categories. Additionally, the respondent could identify, as a write-in, with two races (U. S. Department of Commerce: U. S. Census Bureau 
                     2022
                  ).
